Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 35
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,===============================================================

Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.09,0:01:36.70,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you how we do things at Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.02,0:01:38.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"How you do things at Briggs"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.28,0:01:40.20,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:43.08,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Lend us a hand, alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:45.30,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.30,0:01:46.71,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:49.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on! We're...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:52.51,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You were threatened and forced to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:54.96,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,No one can blame you for that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.42,0:01:57.54,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.54,0:01:59.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's our bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.24,0:02:00.82,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. You're helping, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.45,0:02:03.97,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Pick up the pace! And don't spill any of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:06.83,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Buccaneer! Carry those to Gate 8!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.83,0:02:07.48,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:11.28,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:13.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Shove him into the elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:28.41,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What... a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.85,0:02:32.57,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Push! Push!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.68,0:02:36.26,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,All right! We can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:37.88,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Turret, turn to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:39.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:45.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Miles, send him away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.71,0:02:46.93,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.63,0:02:55.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,All right! We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.99,0:03:07.37,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Where... am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.76,0:03:15.33,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Let him have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:22.05,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:24.97,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.18,0:03:28.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How do we throw him out of the gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.41,0:03:28.27,Default-alt,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,This stuff smells.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.32,0:03:43.82,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Move, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:03:57.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! One more round!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.73,0:03:58.67,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're out of ammo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.83,0:04:00.55,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.65,0:04:05.72,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.60,0:04:14.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.28,0:04:18.36,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It's north-blend fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.04,0:04:24.78,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It vaporizes even in extremely low temperatures,\Nand with that, it absorbs body temperature in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:27.45,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, we're in the middle of a blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:30.35,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,He'll freeze all the way to his brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.98,0:04:34.52,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,So cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:37.29,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,My body...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:41.98,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,...won't... move...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.33,0:04:48.87,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What... a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.69,0:05:00.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Hibernate until spring comes around, dimwit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.76,0:05:04.18,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Buccaneer, haul these three down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.18,0:05:05.09,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.09,0:05:06.11,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.90,0:05:08.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-W-Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.12,0:05:09.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-W-Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.90,0:05:11.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We helped you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.50,0:05:12.11,Default-alt,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,"You were forced to."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:14.12,Default-alt,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that be more convenient for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.02,0:05:20.88,Default-alt,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm not letting you get away until the identity of that monster becomes clear, so be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.77,0:05:31.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:34.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Clang"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:36.96,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.87,0:05:40.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.22,0:05:42.69,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,Yo! Did you have a nice nap?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.43,0:05:45.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I did, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.55,0:05:51.58,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,So I hear you saved our men.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:53.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.85,0:05:55.09,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 100 cenz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:05:58.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't out of gratitude?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:00.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... are there any news?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.87,0:06:03.59,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,The advance unit went to check up on that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.59,0:06:05.59,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,They should be back any moment now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.79,0:06:08.95,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and Major Miles is at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.95,0:06:10.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:13.89,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,He's there to see the guy who was injured while fighting Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.51,0:06:16.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scar is up north, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.70,0:06:18.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:20.17,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,He's awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.17,0:06:21.48,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:23.91,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,You saved our buddies' lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.37,0:06:29.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You guys really care about your buddies, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.93,0:06:32.29,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We at Briggs consider ourselves a monolith.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.29,0:06:35.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And since you saved our buddies, that makes you one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:37.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then can't you let your buddy out of-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.22,0:06:39.00,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,No can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.41,0:06:42.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You guys really are a monolith...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:47.51,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Scar's body wasn't found at the scene of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:50.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There's a possibility he's lurking in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.35,0:06:52.51,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.93,0:06:54.26,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Good lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:58.52,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,First, the cat... and now we also need to search for Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.48,0:07:00.49,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:05.30,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Leave Scar to us and focus on getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.30,0:07:06.73,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:09.65,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I want you all to stay out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.95,0:07:13.16,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,The Ishbalan is my prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:19.29,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately for you, we're not so soft as to let\Na mass murderer do whatever he wants here at Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.01,0:07:22.77,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We believe in the survival of the fittest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.99,0:07:28.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If you let your guard down for a second, you die. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.97,0:07:32.01,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Talk shit again, and you'll never be able to leave the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.63,0:07:38.27,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We at Briggs have been commanded to take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.07,0:07:40.62,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,So stay put.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.40,0:07:48.30,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I remember. Ishbalans are so interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.78,0:07:54.36,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Are you doing all right, Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.05,0:07:58.88,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,You got here sooner than I'd expected, Lieutenant General Raven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:08:01.37,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I rushed here after I heard about your injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.37,0:08:03.38,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,You had me worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.79,0:08:07.59,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you're worried about, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.71,0:08:12.28,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:13.72,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Now, time to get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.04,0:08:16.69,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,But as you can see, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.09,0:08:20.97,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a doctor well-versed in alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.17,0:08:22.97,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,And we have the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:25.50,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be well in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.19,0:08:38.49,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Alchemy is quite difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.75,0:08:42.25,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Especially this whole concept of the "veins of the dragon".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.72,0:08:44.50,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,It's to describe the power running through the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:46.50,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Power running through the earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.07,0:08:49.64,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Simply put,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.64,0:08:55.72,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,it's a power that goes back into the ground after erupting from the summit of a mountain, and enriches the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:59.51,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as a river that runs through the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:04.35,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,By understanding that flow of strength, its entrances and exits...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.10,0:09:11.40,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,You can apply it to practically anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.18,0:09:14.90,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,When you say "anything", does this apply to the human body, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:16.92,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.92,0:09:18.82,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,For example... your hip!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.18,0:09:21.62,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,My foot...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.07,0:09:23.65,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Or, right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.40,0:09:28.75,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I feel that in my eyes after having my neck pressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:31.84,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,You need to take care of your body, Dr. Marcoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.84,0:09:34.42,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,The power in your body is stagnant in many places.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:37.03,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.03,0:09:39.93,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So this is what makes long-distance transmutation possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:44.68,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,So your alchemy doesn't use the veins of the dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.92,0:09:48.88,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We use the energy created by tectonic movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:53.94,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,The immense amount of energy that is released by earthquakes and volcanic activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.20,0:09:57.73,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,This country's alchemy uses that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:09:59.95,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.84,0:10:04.84,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I stepped foot in this country, I felt like something was out of place...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:08.08,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I finally realized what once I went underground in Central...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.64,0:10:11.57,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...but this power, which flows beneath our feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:15.18,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...feels more like it's coming from thousands of people squirming about...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.58,0:10:22.28,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...rather than energy created by tectonic movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.80,0:10:32.69,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.31,0:10:35.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A platoon should be able to get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:39.20,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The tunnel goes on indefinitely, following a loose curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.00,0:10:42.45,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But there aren't any signs of people down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.25,0:10:45.51,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Take the horses down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.51,0:10:46.65,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.65,0:10:48.28,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And bring those three, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.72,0:10:56.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... It really is huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.72,0:11:00.95,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we let him break in without noticing all this was going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.95,0:11:03.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the first time Briggs has been invaded?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.47,0:11:06.22,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Since I came here, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.90,0:11:12.23,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,But around twenty years ago, there was a case when our security guards were attacked during midwinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.93,0:11:17.39,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, a mysterious woman kept stealing food and supplies from them for an entire month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.31,0:11:21.49,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I survived in Briggs in the winter for a month!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:23.11,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be her...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.09,0:11:27.62,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this is far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.24,0:11:29.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.69,0:11:32.62,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:35.62,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry about anyone eavesdropping on us down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:38.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me everything you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.33,0:11:40.63,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I mean everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.14,0:11:43.72,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hide anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:49.76,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked you about the monster, you asked me to try to realize your situation, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:55.35,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,More or less, you believed that I would realize your situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:12:01.40,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You could have been killed at any time in that situation, yet you still summoned those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.83,0:12:05.41,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So I figured you had something to protect,\Neven if it meant you'd lose your life doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:07.41,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,For example, a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.08,0:12:12.41,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to cut the bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.71,0:12:14.20,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.08,0:12:20.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:27.93,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Philosopher's stones... Homunculi...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.51,0:12:32.63,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,King Bradley, and a man who is referred to as Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.63,0:12:34.92,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And the entire upper echelon is guilty....
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.35,0:12:37.60,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,So as we thought, people were being taken hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.44,0:12:42.00,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,A friend of yours who is an automail mechanic and Mustang's men...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.67,0:12:48.38,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We performed many joint drills with Eastern Headquarters, so I know Hawkeye and Havoc.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.04,0:12:51.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It would be a big loss to lose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.48,0:12:52.81,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:56.08,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... what about Colonel Mustang?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.10,0:12:59.71,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... I don't really care about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.23,0:13:04.50,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It would actually be better for me if he just falls, so I have one less rival to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:09.04,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, we need to decide what to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.52,0:13:12.75,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,How do you alchemists see this underground path?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:25.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think this tunnel was dug from Drachma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.60,0:13:32.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is only a hypothesis, but it seems as though this tunnel was dug to create a large circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.54,0:13:33.33,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,A circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:39.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A circle governs the circulation of power in alchemy and is an important factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.46,0:13:42.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now, for the equation...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.16,0:13:49.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Falman, do you know the major incidents within the country that resulted in a lot of bloodshed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.85,0:13:50.97,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Bloodshed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.84,0:13:54.31,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,How would that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.96,0:14:03.73,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Riviere Incident in July of 1558.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:06.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Riviere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.39,0:14:11.14,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The civil war in Cameron in October of 1661.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.97,0:14:15.79,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Soapman incident, February 1799.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.79,0:14:17.21,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,That happened in Fisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.20,0:14:21.79,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Wellsley Conflict, March 1811.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:28.76,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The First Southern Border Conflict occurred in\NOctober of 1835, northwest of where South City is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.58,0:14:34.66,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Second Southern Border Conflict happened in May of 1911, just south of Fortsett.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.34,0:14:36.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What about Pendleton to the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:41.28,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Many soldiers have died there in the battles against Creta, a neighboring nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.66,0:14:45.92,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,And the riot in Liore, in 1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.92,0:14:47.28,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Severe casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.51,0:14:48.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wai-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.52,0:14:50.61,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A riot?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.11,0:14:57.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we report the situation to Eastern Headquarters immediately after we exposed the fake priest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.06,0:14:58.46,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,It was the Central army.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:02.69,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,They came and made the Eastern army withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.69,0:15:06.00,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Liore turned into a mess after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:07.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.31,0:15:08.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.20,0:15:10.78,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Continue what you were doing earlier, Fullmetal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.14,0:15:14.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.36,0:15:20.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're going to connect the dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.62,0:15:24.81,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,How could this be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.03,0:15:29.15,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost identical to the transmutation circle we found under Research Laboratory 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:33.87,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,A circle for creating a philosopher's stone, which uses human lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.14,0:15:39.09,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Just how many people will die with such a large transmutation circle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.10,0:15:46.09,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I once asked Envy if they were trying to create a philosopher's stone using this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:52.09,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But he laughed and told me I was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.67,0:16:00.10,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,In the past, I told Edward that he'd surely be able to realize the real truth, which lies beyond the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.77,0:16:05.63,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,What I meant by the "truth" was that the stones are made of live humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:10.74,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,And what I meant by "beyond the truth" is the existence of the ones behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.96,0:16:16.74,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,And the truth beyond the truth is the transmutation of a philosopher's stone using the entire nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.74,0:16:19.69,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not where it ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:23.47,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what they're planning to do in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:26.75,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We also don't know about immortality, which is what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.40,0:16:30.53,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So you mustn't long for a philosopher's stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.29,0:16:38.31,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx99}We must decipher this research by combining my knowledge of alchemy and your knowledge of Eastern Alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.31,0:16:39.26,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:47.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The oldest one was in 1558...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.87,0:16:50.25,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Right after Amestris was founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.70,0:16:55.62,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Without even a declaration of war, Amestris invaded Riviere, which was once a neighboring country...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.30,0:16:57.03,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.67,0:17:00.03,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.48,0:17:03.45,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The military is involved in every one of these incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.66,0:17:08.40,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The coup d'etat... the civil wars... and Liore, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.84,0:17:11.94,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Central Army came out and poured oil on the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.58,0:17:14.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since this nation was created?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.43,0:17:22.56,Default,Oil,0000,0000,0000,,Our country started out as a small nation, but we expanded by annexing the small countries around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.59,0:17:25.30,Default,Oil,0000,0000,0000,,So it was to create this circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.63,0:17:35.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So it wasn't their plan to use this country to do something, but they created this country to realize their task.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.69,0:17:38.00,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Our country...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.31,0:17:43.41,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mr. Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.41,0:17:47.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He saw the transmutation circle for the stone before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:53.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}Since he worked in the building they have strategy meetings in,\Nhe had access to more resources than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.07,0:17:57.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He was the first to realize there was something wrong with this country-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.65,0:18:01.76,Default,Isaac,0000,0000,0000,,Dog of the military. State Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:05.93,Default,Isaac,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what this country is trying to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.93,0:18:11.31,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think all this prosperity was created with the powers of humans only?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:15.36,Default,Isaac,0000,0000,0000,,If you {\i1}did{\fscx30} {\r} know, you'd understand why I'm doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.72,0:18:19.03,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.26,0:18:23.58,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at the pattern, the next area that will see bloodshed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.92,0:18:28.26,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,The only area left is Briggs!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:32.79,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What do those pigs at Central plan to do with my castle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.79,0:18:34.21,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major General!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.69,0:18:36.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Please return to base at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.56,0:18:39.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant General Raven has come to visit from Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.08,0:18:42.97,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So they're not even giving us time to think, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.44,0:18:45.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:49.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:54.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Could you try and trick Lieutenant General Raven?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.66,0:19:01.59,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for making you wait, Lieutenant General Raven.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.12,0:19:03.76,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,No, worry not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.24,0:19:06.38,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault for coming here without advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.27,0:19:09.79,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Armstrong will be back shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:10.75,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Please, follow me-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.50,0:19:11.66,Default-alt,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.03,0:19:13.63,Default-alt,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought a guest with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.03,0:19:18.37,Default-alt,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles, do you mind giving him a tour of the fort?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.61,0:19:22.47,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:30.34,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Winry's apple pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.71,0:19:34.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The thing I said I'd like to eat when I get my body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.60,0:19:39.32,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we have more important things to think about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.13,0:19:42.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, you'll be able to eat it someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:50.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After we get our bodies back and beat the crap out of those guys planning to use this country for their own goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.15,0:19:52.17,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.49,0:19:56.17,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the mess, Lieutenant General.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.41,0:19:58.62,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We were attacked by the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.62,0:19:59.67,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Attacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.33,0:20:05.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to drive it off,\Nbut the thing was... what you'd call a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.93,0:20:08.26,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.23,0:20:11.43,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't die no matter what we did to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.43,0:20:13.07,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.86,0:20:15.94,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.18,0:20:22.69,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I think it's a biological weapon from Drachma, but the Elric Brothers...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.12,0:20:28.54,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We've taken in the Fullmetal Alchemist and his younger brother by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.50,0:20:34.42,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It seems as though they know something about the monster but won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.35,0:20:42.99,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx98}It could be a disaster if a state alchemist who works with the Führer President is a Drachman spy, so we've arrested them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.99,0:20:44.56,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.04,0:20:46.93,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.14,0:20:49.91,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,They really won't say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.31,0:20:50.93,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.51,0:20:55.69,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They also claim they came here to research organic transmutation or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.69,0:20:59.93,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They're being quite ambiguous. I couldn't doubt them more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:09.68,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I thought about torturing it out of them, but I'm technically a woman, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.19,0:21:12.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't lay a finger on a child like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.08,0:21:14.60,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,My heart would be crushed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.07,0:21:16.24,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.24,0:21:19.11,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,That queen's made of ice to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.18,0:21:26.52,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,So even you, who holds the title of "The Northern Wall of Briggs", has a soft spot for children, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.28,0:21:35.60,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be odd to have a child or two at my age,\Nbut I'm totally behind in those affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.07,0:21:37.30,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.30,0:21:39.30,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,You must be much sought after by the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.66,0:21:40.61,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:45.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a sad experience to age, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.58,0:21:48.36,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely horrified of aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:53.63,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,That biological weapon from Drachma had a wonderful body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.75,0:21:56.33,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,An immortal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:21:58.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it like a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.98,0:22:06.84,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,What if I were to tell you that it may not be long before it isn't just a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.76,0:22:16.18,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Major General...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.31,0:22:21.19,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Are you interested in a perfect, immortal army?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.42,0:22:22.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.73,0:23:59.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,"Obey the ones with power".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.39,0:24:01.74,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That's the true meaning of the law of the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.74,0:24:07.57,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx98}If you don't wish to be bound by that, obtain greater power.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.57,0:24:12.94,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}Because there's always times one must fight power with power.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.67,0:24:17.60,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.75,0:24:21.13,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 36, Family Portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.26,0:24:25.79,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Men set out on journeys with determination in their hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.79,0:24:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
